# container/compliance/ is now COPY'd into each image's `licenses` Dockerfile
# stage (NOTICES generation + license-policy validation), so it must remain
# in the build context. Old comment from prior compliance design left for
# context: was excluded when compliance ran via a separate Dockerfile.extract
# bind-mount; the inline-compliance refactor inverted that intent.
# Local extraction destinations for `docker buildx build --target {legal,sboms}`.
# Excluded from build context so they don't bloat it or leak prior outputs back in.
